http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/other-states/Move-to-raze-temple-sparks-violence-in-Bihar/article14022812.ece

At least eight policemen and several others were injured in a clash between the police and villagers on Tuesday night in Hajipur of Vaishali district where, following a court order, the local police had gone to demolish a roadside temple. The situation remained tense till Wednesday evening.Police said a villager named Kailash Thakur had moved the high court seeking demolition of the Vasudeo temple allegedly erected on encroached land outside his house in Bagmalli . Following a court order, when the police went to demolish it, the villagers opposed it.The villagers got enraged over the move of the district administration and opposed the templeâ€™s demolition. Locals said when the police used mild force to disperse the gathered mob, the villagers too attacked policemen and chased them away from the spot. Altogether eight policemen, two fire brigade officials and some villagers got injured in the violent clash. The enraged mob of villagers also set a police vehicle and two tractors on fire. The injured were admitted to the local town hospital.